## Mandatory delegation packet (orchestrator → subagent)

Subagents **do not** see this chat. For **every** `/coder`, `/code-tester`, and `/doc` invocation, paste a single block at the top of the delegation prompt (fill every field; use `n/a` only when truly not applicable). For **`/tester`** (E2E harness only), use the same block shape; set **`subagent: tester`** and include any **`e2e_workflow`** / harness fields the task references (see **`.cursor/agents/tester.md`**, **TASK-064**).

```text
## Delegation packet (orchestrator → subagent)
- subagent: coder | code-tester | doc  |  (E2E only: subagent: tester)
- task_file: <absolute or repo-relative path to docs/tasks/active/*.md>
- spec_refs: <e.g. project_spec.md §9 TASK-XXX, §7.1 — copy verbatim lines the subagent must obey>
- legacy_reference: <copy Legacy Reference table/lines from the task file, or "none">
- user_constraints: <copy any user messages that limit scope; or "none">
- prior_artifacts: <if chaining: paste full prior Output Contract JSON/text from coder or code-tester; or "none" for coder>
- files_changed_prior: <from coder/code-tester payload; list paths; or "none" for coder>
- verification_extras: <e.g. "run: bash scripts/ci/check-repo-integrity.sh" when task touches manifest/required-paths/scripts/ci; else "default: test.sh + lint.sh only">
- one_line_goal: <single sentence>
```

**Rules**

- Do **not** summarize the task file into one sentence instead of pasting **`spec_refs`** and **`legacy_reference`** when the task file contains them — the subagent must receive the same constraints you used to plan.
- For **`/coder`**: include **`prior_artifacts: none`** and the **full path** to the active task file; the subagent must **read the entire task file** from disk, not rely on partial quotes.
- For **`/code-tester`**: include **`files_changed_prior`** and the **coder Output Contract** (full) under **`prior_artifacts`**.
- For **`/doc`**: include **code-tester Output Contract** (full) under **`prior_artifacts`**, plus **`files_changed_prior`** (merge coder + code-tester lists if both changed files).

