## Hybrid workflow: inline (this session) vs subagents (isolated)

**Default for this repo:** **subagents** (isolated sub-sessions) for **`/coder` → `/code-tester` → `/doc`** unless the user says **`same session, inline`** for that task.

| Mode | When to use | Behavior |
|------|-------------|----------|
| **Subagent pipeline (default)** | Always, unless the user has said **`same session, inline`** (case-insensitive; comma optional) for **this** task | After approval, invoke **`/coder` → `/code-tester` → `/doc`** with **Delegation packets** as above. |
| **Inline (main session)** | User said **`same session, inline`** (or **`same session inline`**) for this task | Implement **in this chat** without spawning `/coder` / `/code-tester` / `/doc`, **provided**: you still honor **approval gates** when the task would normally require them; you still run **`bash .cursor/skills/test.sh`** and **`bash .cursor/skills/lint.sh`** (and **`bash scripts/ci/check-repo-integrity.sh`** when manifest/ci paths change) yourself and report results before claiming done; you still update **README/docs** in-thread if behavior changed. **Do not** use inline mode to skip tests or user approval gates. |

If the user is **ambiguous** (no **`same session, inline`**), use the **subagent pipeline** — including for **single-file** edits and **small** changes.

